  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nThe user opens an chatbot, then it goes elsewhere on status, then he comes back to the chatbot. It would be nice to be able to listen to that event in order to propose suggestions or just say \"hi again\"\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: An addListener that respond to the event of a user reopening the chatbot window (the init only handles the opening of the chatbot after restarting status)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\nBeing able to respond to the action of reopening a chatbot\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nWe only have the \"init\" addListener which is quite limited in terms of UX\r\n",
